<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-07T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-07T03:00:00-05:00" n="517" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/12–748: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Krentz</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-07T16:00:00+08:00">December
                                    7, 1948—4 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 7—5:11 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>91. Estimate about 40,000 refugees arrived here to date all classes
                            carrying large amounts US [currency?] and gold bars. Key money rates
                            soaring Taipei; 3-room Jap house US 10,000.</p>
                        <p>Far as known no very big names except Chen Kuo-fu<note n="2" xml:id="d517fn2">Member of the Kuomintang Central Executive
                                Committee.</note> but mostly families [with] connections Taiwan
                            officials, plus merchants, professional and secondary mainland officials
                            families. Some advance CAF<note n="3" xml:id="d517fn3">Chinese Air
                                Force.</note> arrivals.</p>
                        <p>Sent Nanking 179, repeated Department 91.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Krentz</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>